{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847994349,"sessionID":"ses_28736e7f2ffeEts0AnLu9CCUI3","part":{"id":"prt_d78c9839f001LUaD7kePUdo2x0","messageID":"msg_d78c97495001gxSQ9lq1e5dKar","sessionID":"ses_28736e7f2ffeEts0AnLu9CCUI3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_1d069a1490c546d49dacfa0c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n\n**Module:** pkg/router  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement HTTP reverse proxy core functionality for the pkg/router module.\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n- [ ] Design reverse proxy architecture\n- [ ] Implement proxy core logic\n- [ ] Add routing rules engine\n- [ ] Add connection pooling\n- [ ] Add health checks\n- [ ] Add unit tests\n- [ ] Add integration tests\n\n## Notes\n\nSee `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.\n\n## Source Files\n\nSee `src/` directory for source code changes.\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/README.md","time":{"start":1775847994318,"end":1775847994347}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847994352,"sessionID":"ses_28736e7f2ffeEts0AnLu9CCUI3","part":{"id":"prt_d78c99394001q3myTFwh27n6LH","messageID":"msg_d78c97495001gxSQ9lq1e5dKar","sessionID":"ses_28736e7f2ffeEts0AnLu9CCUI3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_c6b9e1ec8d064c7eb1ab023f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"{\n  \"ar\": \"AR-009\",\n  \"title\": \"Router HTTP 反向代理核心\",\n  \"module\": \"pkg/router\",\n  \"language\": \"Go\",\n  \"size\": \"M\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"created\": \"2026-04-11\",\n  \"completed\": null\n}\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/status.json"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/status.json","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/status.json","time":{"start":1775847994328,"end":1775847994350}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847994356,"sessionID":"ses_28736e7f2ffeEts0AnLu9CCUI3","part":{"id":"prt_d78c99fe00011ro15l1fMjhBwi","messageID":"msg_d78c97495001gxSQ9lq1e5dKar","sessionID":"ses_28736e7f2ffeEts0AnLu9CCUI3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_2e588fcd9d8240d78f34c4ec","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Proxy Configuration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `ProxyConfig` struct in `pkg/router/proxy/config.go`\n  - Fields: `TargetURL` (string), `Timeout` (time.Duration), `MaxIdleConns` (int), `IdleConnTimeout` (time.Duration), `ResponseHeaderTimeout` (time.Duration)\n  - Document each field with comments\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `DefaultProxyConfig()` function\n  - Returns default configuration with sensible timeouts\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `RouteRule` struct in `pkg/router/proxy/route.go`\n  - Fields: `Path` (string), `Method` (string), `Target` (string), `StripPrefix` (bool), `Headers` (map[string]string)\n  - Methods: `Match()`, `Apply()`\n\n### Phase 2: Proxy Core\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `ReverseProxy` struct in `pkg/router/proxy/proxy.go`\n  - Fields: `config`, `transport`, `routes`, `metrics`, `logger`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewReverseProxy()` constructor\n  - Takes config and optional routes\n  - Returns initialized *ReverseProxy\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `ServeHTTP()` method\n  - Matches incoming request to route\n  - Forwards request to target\n  - Streams response back to client\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `proxyRequest()` method\n  - Copies request headers\n  - Handles body streaming\n  - Manages connection lifecycle\n\n- [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `AddRoute()` and `RemoveRoute()` methods\n  - Thread-safe route management\n\n### Phase 3: Health Checks\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `HealthChecker` struct in `pkg/router/proxy/health.go`\n  - Fields: `interval`, `timeout`, `unhealthyThreshold`, `targets` (map[string]*TargetHealth)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `Start()` and `Stop()` methods\n  - Periodic health checking\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `checkTarget()` method\n  - HTTP GET to health endpoint\n  - Updates target health status\n\n- [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `GetHealthyTargets()` method\n  - Returns list of healthy targets for routing\n\n### Phase 4: Connection Pooling\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `ConnectionPool` in `pkg/router/proxy/pool.go`\n  - Manages reusable connections to targets\n  - Configurable max connections per target\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `GetConnection()` and `ReleaseConnection()` methods\n  - Connection acquisition and release\n\n### Phase 5: Metrics\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `ProxyMetrics` struct in `pkg/router/proxy/metrics.go`\n  - Fields: `requestsTotal` (Counter), `requestDuration` (Histogram), `activeConnections` (Gauge), `errorsTotal` (Counter), `upstreamHealth` (GaugeVec)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement metric recording methods\n  - `recordRequest()`, `recordError()`, `updateConnectionCount()`\n\n### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestReverseProxy_ServeHTTP` in `pkg/router/proxy/proxy_test.go`\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestReverseProxy_RouteMatching`\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestHealthChecker_CheckTarget`\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestConnectionPool_GetConnection`\n- [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestProxyMetrics_RecordRequest`\n- [ ] **TEST-006**: Integration test with mock upstream server\n\n### Phase 7: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/router/proxy/doc.go`\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Update `pkg/router/README.md`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Reverse proxy forwards requests to configured targets\n- [ ] Route matching works correctly\n- [ ] Health checks detect unhealthy targets\n- [ ] Connection pooling reduces connection overhead\n- [ ] Metrics exported for Prometheus\n- [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n- [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.5\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown implemented\n- [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- **Required**: None (core router functionality)\n- **Optional**: Prometheus client for metrics\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775847994334,"end":1775847994353}}}}
